cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the competition between providers in terms of network performance, capacity constraints, cost reductions, and revenue prospects in the context of Wi-Fi offloading. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses game theory to analyze the competition, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as the second likely category. The paper also discusses the use of unlicensed spectrum, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper mentions the potential for tragedy-of-commons type of problems, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
